The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Mzansi is
3034. Health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said that today “we
regrettably report 2 new COVID-19 related deaths. “We convey our condolences to
the families and we urge the public to take preventive measures. Stay at home
unless it’s essential.” This takes the death toll to 52 with the highest number
reported in KZN. There has been a total of 903 recoveries. Mzansi has so far conducted 108 021 tests around the
country. 